This paper is about improving the computational efficiency of query processing in graph databases through learning to speed up query planning. The paper discusses the use of a learning framework to improve the search behavior of query reasoners, which is a problem that falls under the categories of database systems (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG).
